<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n41042b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41042b">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41042b"> 42(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> libel &amp; slander</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Defamation consists in the publication without justification or excuse of that which is calculated to expose another to hatred, contempt or ridicule, or to convey an imputation on a person disparaging him in his trade, business, profession, calling or office. If the publication is written or printed words or in any other permanent form it is a <mark>libel</mark>; if by word only it is a <mark>slander</mark>. <small> Maud I. Crofts, <a name="MICW" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MICW"><cite title="source">Women under English Law</cite></a>, 1st ed. (1925) 88</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
